Large parts of Pietermaritzburg were without power on Tuesday following several electricity faults. Msunduzi Municipality issued an electricity update listing some of the outages the City was attending to. The City said there was a trip at the Retief primary substation and at Townbush Grey's Hospital substation that is affecting part of Montrose and Chase Valley. There is also a trip at the Mason primary substation that is affecting the transit area, Wigford, Tannery, Herchenson, Sutherland and surrounding roads. Msunduzi said it is also attending to another trip at Alabaster/Nickel that is affecting Copesville, Haniville, Bishopstowe and surrounding areas. The City said it is attending to several other electricity faults across town that affect areas including Ezinkatheni, Darjeeling, Orient heights, Bombay Heights, Grange, Westgate, Foxhill, Mpumelelo, Parts of Bisley, Claridge, Nhlalakahle, Balhambra, Stock, Barbet, Swallow, Muniredy, Woodpecker, Flamingo,Upper CBD, Mpumuza, Prestbury, Blackridge, Wembley, Athlone,
Morcom rd, old Howick, Uplands, Mayor's Walk, Zwartkop, Parts of Dennis Shepston Rd and surrounding areas. Msunduzi said single complaints are attended to as and when logged via the call center or faults office. The City went on to apologise for any inconvenience caused. 